HEADWORD: Charmel
<hw>Char"mel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.]</ety>
<def>A fruitful field.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Libanus shall be turned into <qex>charmel</qex>, and
<qex>charmel</qex> shall be esteemed as a forest.</q> <rj><qau>Isa.
xxix. 17 (Douay version).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

